@rjernst @benwtrent sorry for the noise as I was not planning to update this PR yet.
I wonder if it makes sense to provide a formatted value in the null case - we're obscuring the fact that there is no value there, plus making it quite involved to get it to work right for every possible date format, as min / max values for dates will depend on a potential custom date format the user is using. Should we just return null and not do any date formatting?
I understand about bwc - but IIUC this is already returning an error for users that hit this use case, so I don't think there is a proper client handling in this case that we should worry about?

